{{distinguish|Kili language (Gabon)|Kili language (Congo)}} {{Infobox language |name=Kili |altname=Kur-Urmi |states=Russia, China |speakers=40 |date=1989–1990 |ref={{citation needed|date=August 2013}} |familycolor=Altaic |fam1=[[Tungusic languages|Tungusic]] |fam2=Northern? |fam3=Evenki group |iso3=none |glotto=kile1243 |glottorefname=Kilen }}
'''Kili''' (Kirin, Kila), known as ''Hezhe'' or more specifically ''Qileen (奇勒恩 Qílè'ēn)'' in Chinese and also as the Kur-Urmi dialect of [[Nanai language|Nanai]], is a [[Tungusic language]] of Russia and China. Nanai is a Southern Tungusic language, and Kili has traditionally been considered one of the diverse dialects of Nanai, but it "likely belongs to the northern group".<ref>Alexander Vovin, "Tungusic Languages", in the ''Encyclopedia of Language and Linguistics'', 2006</ref>
