'''''The Ballad of Angel's Alley''''' is a musical set in Melbourne's 'push' wars of the 1890s, with book and lyrics by Jeff Underhill and music by Bruce George.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Pinne|first=Peter|year=2010|title=The Ballad of Angel's Alley|url=https://www.theatreheritage.org.au/images/OnStage/backissues/2010-4.pdf|journal=On Stage|volume=Spring 2010|pages=8–11|via=}}</ref>

First seen at Melbourne's New Theatre in 1958, ''The Ballad of Angel's Alley'' received a professional premiere in July 1962 at the [[Russell Street Theatre|Russell St Theatre]] in Melbourne presented by the [[Union Theatre Repertory Company]]. Subsequent professional revivals included Sydney's [[Old Tote Theatre Company]] in September 1963 and Melbourne's [[Melbourne Little Theatre|St Martin's Theatre]] in April 1973.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ausstage.edu.au/pages/work/1646|title=AusStage - The Ballad of Angel's Alley|last=|first=|date=|website=www.ausstage.edu.au|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-03-19}}</ref>

The script was published by Yackandandah Playscripts in 1989.

